Tailoring the generic service type abstraction level shall consist of:  
ewline 1. adding mission-specific service types; 
ewline 2. adding mission-specific subservice types; 
ewline 3. adding mission-specific capability types; 
ewline 4. adding mission-specific message types.

For each on-board memory, the following characteristics of that memory shall be declared when specifying that memory: 
ewline 1. the memory access alignment constraint; 
ewline 2. the memory size, in bytes; 
ewline 3. the allowed operations; 
ewline 4. the addressing scheme.

When declaring the characteristics of an on-board memory, the allowed operations shall be one of the following: 
ewline 1. "read only"; 
ewline 2. "read and write"; 
ewline 3. "write only".

Each request shall be uniquely identified by a request identifier that is the combination of: 
ewline 1. a source identifier that corresponds to the application process user identifier of the application process that hosts the subservice user that generates that request; 
ewline 2. a destination identifier that corresponds to the combination of the application process identifier of the application process that hosts the subservice provider that is responsible for executing that request and the system identifier of the system that hosts that application process; 
ewline 3. a sequence count or request name that is produced by the application process that hosts the subservice user.

Each request shall contain: 
ewline 1. a flag indicating whether the reporting of the successful acceptance of that request by the destination application process is requested; 
ewline 2. a flag indicating whether the reporting of the successful start of execution of that request by the destination application process is requested; 
ewline 3. a flag indicating whether the reporting of the successful progresses of execution of that request by the destination application process is requested; 
ewline 4. a flag indicating whether the reporting of the successful completion of execution of that request by the destination application process is requested.

For each request that it receives, the subservice provider in charge of the execution of that request shall, in sequence: 
ewline 1. if the pre-conditions for the execution of that request are not fulfilled: 
ewline (a) notify the execution reporting subservice of its parent application process of the failed start of execution; 
ewline (b) stop processing that request; 
ewline 2. if the pre-conditions for the execution of that request are fulfilled, 
ewline notify the execution reporting subservice of its parent application process of the successful start of execution; 
ewline 3. for each step, if any: 
ewline (a) verify the execution conditions of that step, if any; 
ewline (b) if the execution conditions of that step are not fulfilled, notify the execution reporting subservice of its parent application process of the failed progress of execution of that step; 
ewline (c) if the step's execution conditions are fulfilled, notify the execution reporting subservice of its parent application process of the successful progress of execution of that step; 
ewline at the end of the execution of that request: newline (a) verify the post-conditions of execution, if any; 
ewline (b) if any step execution has failed or if the post-conditions of execution are not fulfilled, notify the execution reporting subservice of its parent application process of the failed completion of execution and stop processing that request; 
ewline (c) if the post-conditions of execution are fulfilled, notify the execution reporting subservice of its parent application process of the successful completion of execution;

Each report shall be uniquely identified by a report identifier that is the combination of: 
ewline 1. a source identifier that is the application process identifier of the application process that hosts the subservice provider that generates that report; 
ewline 2. a destination identifier that corresponds to the application process user identifier of the application process that hosts the subservice user that is responsible for processing that report; 
ewline 3. a source sequence count that is produced by the application process that hosts the subservice provider.

Deploying the service topology of an overall space system should consist of: 
ewline 1. specifying new implementations of PUS services by instantiating the service types and related components; 
ewline 2. assessing the adequacy of reusing existing service implementations: (a) ensuring their compliance to the PUS standard services; 
ewline (b) verifying their compliance to the overall system constraints.

Each failed routing notification shall contain: 
ewline 1. the identifier of the request that failed the routing verification; 
ewline 2. the failure notice made of: 
ewline (a) a failure code; 
ewline auxiliary data, if any, used to explain the reason for the failed routing.

Each failed acceptance notification shall contain: 
ewline 1. the identifier of the request that failed the acceptance verification; 
ewline 2. the failure notice made of: 
ewline (a) a failure code; 
ewline (b) auxiliary data, if any, used to explain the reason for the failed acceptance.

Each housekeeping parameter report structure shall consist of: 
ewline 1. a housekeeping parameter report structure identifier; 
ewline 2. the collection interval used to generate the corresponding reports; 
ewline 3. an ordered list of zero or more simply commutated parameters; 
ewline 4. an ordered list of zero or more super commutated parameter sets, each set consisting of: 
ewline (a) the number of sampled values to report for each parameter of that set, and 
ewline (b) the ordered list of one or more parameters contained within that set; 
ewline if the housekeeping reporting subservice provides the capability for managing the periodic generation of housekeeping parameter reports, a status indicating whether the periodic generation action of the corresponding housekeeping parameter reports is enabled or disabled.

Each housekeeping parameter notification shall contain: 
ewline 1. the housekeeping parameter report structure identifier; 
ewline 2. in the specified order for simply commutated parameters, a single sampled value for each simply commutated parameter; 
ewline 3. in the specified order for super commutated parameter sets, for each super commutated parameter set: 
ewline (a) the "super commutated sample repetition number" sets of sampled values.

Each instruction to create a housekeeping parameter report structure shall contain: 
ewline 1. the housekeeping parameter report structure identifier to create; 
ewline 2. the collection interval; 
ewline 3. the list of simply commutated parameters in the required order; 
ewline 4. the list of super commutated parameter sets in the required order.

The housekeeping reporting subservice shall reject any request to create a housekeeping parameter report structure if any of the following conditions occurs: 
ewline 1. that request contains an instruction that refers to a housekeeping parameter report structure that is already in use; 
ewline 2. the same parameter is identified more than once in that request; 
ewline 3. the resources allocated to the hosting of housekeeping parameter report structures are exceeded.

For each valid instruction to report a housekeeping parameter report structure, the housekeeping reporting subservice shall generate a single housekeeping parameter report structure report that contains exactly one housekeeping parameter report structure notification that includes: 
ewline 1. the housekeeping parameter report structure identifier; 
ewline 2. If the housekeeping reporting subservice provides the capability for managing the periodic generation of housekeeping parameter reports, the periodic generation action status; 
ewline 3. the collection interval; 
ewline 4. the ordered list of simply commutated parameters; 
ewline 5. the ordered list of super commutated parameter sets. 86
